fect your account if you are the original owner of the account. If you are NOT the original owner of this account, this WILL still work and this method will change the registering information to your information! Please follow the rules carefully. You are not losing any money by doing this…<br><br>1. Go to the Everquest website and Sign up for EQ Legends server. (You are not losing any money by doing this.) This is also great for seeing who registered your account if you aren’t the original owner. It will ask you to login and a sign up page will pop up. Half of the sign up form will be filled in already for you with the person that first registered your account. Above this information it will state if you aren’t the first register for this account, you can’t register for EQ Legends. That information is false. Verant would love to get paid $40/month instead of $10 a month, anyone can sign up.  If the name is the same as yours, keep it the same, if its different, fill in your name and information and click the sign up button. You actually just updated your info on your EQ account. (YOU ARE EVEN ABLE TO TRANSFER BOUGHT CHARACTERS TO YOUR REGISTERED EQ ACCOUNTS!) I have tested this and I have even called in a junk account of mine and changed the password. I gave them the info I registered with and they gave me my password back without having to give the original CD Keys. They use the last 4-digits of your credit card to verify that the account is yours. <br><br>2. You will receive an email to confirm you email address, simply follow the directions. You will then get an email saying they are reviewing your info to see if you will get accepted to the EQ Legends server. Everyone gets a reply back saying you qualify. Follow the directions and the character server change form. You can move 1 or all of your characters at no extra charge to EQ Legends. (YES YOU CAN GO BACK TO YOUR OLD SERVER) Move the character or character’s that you would like to get your name changed. They will be moved the same day usually. Go on your server that your character was originally from and either you or a friend on a different account make a newbie or new character with the same name your character that got transferred to the other server with. Example: You transfer character X from server Tallon to the Legends server. Make a new character on Tallon named just like character X. You name is taken now, simply go to your billing on the Everquest sign in screen and press cancel account, which makes it so you wont get billed every month. (You aren’t destroying your account; you are only canceling your Legends service.) Send an email to EQLegends email address found on the Everquest website and say you wish to go back to your old server. They will reply and say they put your name in the files to be switched back to your original server. When you are switched back you will arrive in game with your same name with an “x” at the end. Example: if your name was Trick, it will now be Trickx. Simply petition saying you got switched back to Rallos and your name was taken, they will ask you what you would like for your new name and Walla…its changed. <br><br>This method works! If you are wondering about the money you registered with for Legends, which is going towards your standard billing of $10. You lost nothing. It takes a little bit of your time, but in the end you have a new rep and it beats leveling up a new character or signing on everyday disliking your name. Enjoy!<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/usinneed.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinneed</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(4/4/02 11:15:57 am)</font><br>   <a